 argues that learning to heal requires us to desire and value healing as a vital possibility. With this book, Cohen advocates reviving healing’s role for all those whose lives are touched by illness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aCrohn's diseasexAlternative treatment. 0aCrohn's diseasexPatients. 0aHealingxPhilosophy. 0aMental healing. 0aMind and body. 0aSelf-care, Health. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Diseases / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023944?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023944/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles